parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to remain in park can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle slips out of park and into reverse
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly
the transmission does not shift properly
the vehicle shuts off without warning
the gearshift lever indicator is not in the correct position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to provide necessary parts or tools to dealerships can delay or prevent repairs, leaving vehicles with potentially hazardous transmission issues on the road.
symptoms: Dealerships are unable to perform recall repairs due to lack of parts or tools
consumers are not notified of recalls
recall repairs are incomplete or ineffective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission fluid leaks can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaks
the transmission does not shift properly
the vehicle shuts off without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line corrosion/rusting can cause brake fluid leakage, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
no braking action
brake fluid leakage
rust or corrosion on brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS failure can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries, especially in wet or snowy conditions.
symptoms: ABS light comes on
vehicle moves when brakes are applied
rear brakes do not engage
brake pedal feels light or spongy
brakes lock up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Master cylinder failure can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
no braking action
brake fluid leakage
master cylinder push rod snaps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake rotor/caliper failure can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake rotors are warped or rusted
brake calipers are faulty
brake pads are worn out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rear brakes do not engage
rear brake adjustment lever is not touching the brake shoes
rear brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents, especially when driving on highways or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine quits or stalls without warning
sometimes while idling
and sometimes while driving; the vehicle may start right up again or require cranking for a while before starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or even catch fire, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls or quits without warning; the vehicle's lights flicker or turn off; the vehicle's electrical equipment continues to run after the ignition is turned off; the wiring harness catches on fire; the circuit panel on the dashboard has an electrical short.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring and terminals can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or even catch fire, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Burnt terminals and wiring; the backup lamps do not function; the wiring harness catches on fire; the circuit panel on the dashboard has an electrical short.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or even catch fire, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The distributor cap and rotor fail
causing loss of power; the ignition coil fails
causing the vehicle to stall unexpectedly.
